A Functional Interface in Java:
Has exactly one abstract method.
Can have default and static methods.
Can be used with lambda expressions or method references.
Annotated with @FunctionalInterface



Built-in functional interfaces:
Function<T,R> → takes T, returns R
BiFunction<T, U, R> -> Takes two inputs (T and U) and returns one output (R).
Consumer<T> → takes T, returns void
Supplier<T> → returns T
Predicate<T> → returns boolean
UnaryOperator<T> → takes and returns same type
BinaryOperator<T> → takes two arguments of same type and returns same type